Shawn I am praveen working in Integration testing using Junit and Ant. I faced the same problem which you have. you have to design a specification i.e your junit client progam should
name with e.g ClientTest.java & all the test methods (e.g test_01 or test_dbcheck) 

When you execute your test cases using ant, the execute command should use the ant build file. from the build file it should use &quot;unit test&quot; if your doing unit testing from there it should identify i.e which Java programs should execute and how the result format will be.

I am doing integration testing so when i execute my junit client using ant. At the time of execution it refers to &quot;integration test&quot; and not the &quot;unit test&quot;.

For more reference read &quot;Ant tool&quot; and understand about the build XML File. 

